### Description

Sorry if this was already proposed (or something similar). Since [this feature](https://github.com/angular/angular/pull/49633 ) was introduced it makes sense (to me) that there would be an `@Output()` binding counter-part. 

### Proposed solution

```
export class CounterComponent {  
  @Input({ transform: numberAttribute }) currentCount = 0;
  @Output({ queryParam: true }) currentCountChange = new EventEmitter<number>();

  incrementCounter() {
    this.currentCountChange.emit(++this.currentCount);
  }
}
```
Some notes about this use-case/solution:
- it would be nice if the default functionality was to use the output name (without "Change") as the query parameter name.
- it would be nice/necessary to allow a different name for the query parameter (`@Output({ queryParam: 'current-count' })`)

### Alternatives considered

This works today but is dog-gone verbose.

```
export class CounterComponent {  
  @Input({ transform: numberAttribute }) currentCount = 0;

  private readonly route = inject(ActivatedRoute);
  private readonly router = inject(Router);

  incrementCounter() {
    this.router.navigate([], {
      relativeTo: this.route,
      queryParamsHandling: "merge",
      queryParams: {
        currentCount : ++this.currentCount,
      } satisfies Partial<CounterComponent>,
    });
  }
}

