### Description

After poking around with `@error`, i have come to the conclusion that it only works when the deferred file doesn't load.

I would like if `@defer` also worked with an `Observable`, so that it would `subscribe` on the `Observable` similarly to `AsyncPipe` and, where it would also go to `@error` if the `Observable` `throws` an `error`

The `@error` could be combined with this issue https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/52800

And using `as` syntax is also requested here https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/52898

### Proposed solution

```html
@defer(when observable; as result) {
   <result-cmp [data]=result></result-cmp>
} @placeholder {
   <skeleton-cmp></skeleton-cmp>
} @loading {
   <animating-skeleton-cmp></animating-skeleton-cmp>
} @error(err) {
   <div>
       <span>It failed to load component</span>
       <button click="retryDefer()">Reload</button>
   </div>
}
``` 

### Alternatives considered

When the `Observable` fails or when the an `error` is `thrown` inside the deferred component, it doesn't end up in the `@error` block, so as of now i don't think it is possible
